<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1279,2026]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1460,1486]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Morphology.</emphasis>
Vase-shaped sponge, without a well-developed oscular fringe. Surface strongly hispid due to a dense mat of very long diactines, which point down towards the base of the sponge (
<figureCitation box="[1088,1185,1496,1522]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1402,438,1864]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[151,1402,438,1864]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 14A–F. Megapogon villosus. A: preserved cotype BMNH-1907.8.6.151. B–C: histological section including cortical layer, choanosome and atrial cavity. D–E: SEM images of cortical layer. F: SEM image of choanosome section, including cortical layer, choanosome and atrial cavity. Abbreviations: At = atrial cavity; Chc = choanocyte chambers; Chi = chiactines; Cor = cortical layer/cortex; Di = diactines; Mic = microdiactines; Os = osculum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3244658/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Fig 14A</figureCitation>
). The 
<typeStatus box="[1253,1356,1496,1522]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">lectotype</typeStatus>
is 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.46" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="14.6">14.6 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[266,401,1532,1558]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.7" metricValueMax="7.8" metricValueMin="3.6" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="5.7" valueMax="7.8" valueMin="3.6">3.6–7.8 mm</quantity>
wide, and 
<quantity box="[523,658,1532,1558]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="11.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="0.95" valueMax="1.1" valueMin="0.8">0.8–1.1 mm</quantity>
thick. Colour beige in ethanol. Aquiferous system seems to be leuconoid with rounded choanocyte chambers scattered in the mesohyl (
<figureCitation box="[899,983,1568,1594]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1402,438,1864]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[151,1402,438,1864]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 14A–F. Megapogon villosus. A: preserved cotype BMNH-1907.8.6.151. B–C: histological section including cortical layer, choanosome and atrial cavity. D–E: SEM images of cortical layer. F: SEM image of choanosome section, including cortical layer, choanosome and atrial cavity. Abbreviations: At = atrial cavity; Chc = choanocyte chambers; Chi = chiactines; Cor = cortical layer/cortex; Di = diactines; Mic = microdiactines; Os = osculum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3244658/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Figs 14</figureCitation>
B–C).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="34" lastPageNumber="235" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1279,2026]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,1603,1630]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Skeleton.</emphasis>
Cortical skeleton composed of tangentially arranged triactines, and a dense mat of long diactines that cross the surface (
<figureCitation box="[350,448,1640,1666]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1402,438,1864]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[151,1402,438,1864]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 14A–F. Megapogon villosus. A: preserved cotype BMNH-1907.8.6.151. B–C: histological section including cortical layer, choanosome and atrial cavity. D–E: SEM images of cortical layer. F: SEM image of choanosome section, including cortical layer, choanosome and atrial cavity. Abbreviations: At = atrial cavity; Chc = choanocyte chambers; Chi = chiactines; Cor = cortical layer/cortex; Di = diactines; Mic = microdiactines; Os = osculum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3244658/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Fig 14D</figureCitation>
). Smaller and spiny microdiactines are placed around the inhalant pores (
<figureCitation box="[1260,1354,1640,1666]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1402,438,1864]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[151,1402,438,1864]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 14A–F. Megapogon villosus. A: preserved cotype BMNH-1907.8.6.151. B–C: histological section including cortical layer, choanosome and atrial cavity. D–E: SEM images of cortical layer. F: SEM image of choanosome section, including cortical layer, choanosome and atrial cavity. Abbreviations: At = atrial cavity; Chc = choanocyte chambers; Chi = chiactines; Cor = cortical layer/cortex; Di = diactines; Mic = microdiactines; Os = osculum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3244658/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Fig 14E</figureCitation>
). In the choanoskeleton there are chiactines and triactines with their unpaired actines that can project through the surface (
<figureCitation box="[159,243,1712,1738]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1402,438,1864]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[151,1402,438,1864]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 14A–F. Megapogon villosus. A: preserved cotype BMNH-1907.8.6.151. B–C: histological section including cortical layer, choanosome and atrial cavity. D–E: SEM images of cortical layer. F: SEM image of choanosome section, including cortical layer, choanosome and atrial cavity. Abbreviations: At = atrial cavity; Chc = choanocyte chambers; Chi = chiactines; Cor = cortical layer/cortex; Di = diactines; Mic = microdiactines; Os = osculum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3244658/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Figs 14</figureCitation>
C–F). The atrial skeleton comprises chiactines with their long unpaired actines pointing towards, and often projecting through the cortex (
<figureCitation box="[492,575,1748,1774]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1402,438,1864]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[151,1402,438,1864]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 14A–F. Megapogon villosus. A: preserved cotype BMNH-1907.8.6.151. B–C: histological section including cortical layer, choanosome and atrial cavity. D–E: SEM images of cortical layer. F: SEM image of choanosome section, including cortical layer, choanosome and atrial cavity. Abbreviations: At = atrial cavity; Chc = choanocyte chambers; Chi = chiactines; Cor = cortical layer/cortex; Di = diactines; Mic = microdiactines; Os = osculum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3244658/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Figs 14</figureCitation>
C–F). The atrial wall is supported by the paired actines of the chiactines, and among them some triactines and microdiactines can be found (
<figureCitation box="[852,950,1783,1810]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1137,1162]" captionTargetBox="[151,1402,166,1117]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[151,1402,166,1117]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 15A–D: Megapogon villosus. A: SEM image of atrial layer. B–D: SEM images of spicules; fragmented diactine and cortical triactines (B), microdiactine (C), chiactine (D). Abbreviations: Chi = chiactines; Ctr = cortical triactines; Di= diactines; Mic = microdiactines; Exa = exhalant aperture; Tri = triactines." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3244660/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Fig 15A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1279,2026]" box="[199,1422,1819,1846]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,304,1819,1846]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Spicules.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[311,418,1821,1846]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Diactines</emphasis>
: very long and straight with sharp points. Most of them were broken (
<figureCitation box="[1204,1299,1819,1846]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1137,1162]" captionTargetBox="[151,1402,166,1117]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[151,1402,166,1117]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 15A–D: Megapogon villosus. A: SEM image of atrial layer. B–D: SEM images of spicules; fragmented diactine and cortical triactines (B), microdiactine (C), chiactine (D). Abbreviations: Chi = chiactines; Ctr = cortical triactines; Di= diactines; Mic = microdiactines; Exa = exhalant aperture; Tri = triactines." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3244660/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Fig 15B</figureCitation>
, 
<tableCitation box="[1310,1408,1820,1846]" captionStart="TABLE 11" captionStartId="34.[151,239,874,898]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="TABLE 11. Spicule measurements of Megapogon villosus (lectotype BMNH-1907.8.6.146). Measurements from the original description by Jenkin (1908) are included below." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/8DE99893FFF7FF9AE994D257FD6F4FC3" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" tableUuid="8DE99893FFF7FF9AE994D257FD6F4FC3">Table 11</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1279,2026]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis box="[199,367,1856,1882]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Microdiactines</emphasis>
: small and slightly bent diactines. Some smooth, and some with spines. One end lanceolate, and the other hastate (
<figureCitation box="[350,454,1892,1918]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1883,1908]" captionTargetBox="[151,1402,438,1864]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[151,1402,438,1864]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 14A–F. Megapogon villosus. A: preserved cotype BMNH-1907.8.6.151. B–C: histological section including cortical layer, choanosome and atrial cavity. D–E: SEM images of cortical layer. F: SEM image of choanosome section, including cortical layer, choanosome and atrial cavity. Abbreviations: At = atrial cavity; Chc = choanocyte chambers; Chi = chiactines; Cor = cortical layer/cortex; Di = diactines; Mic = microdiactines; Os = osculum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3244658/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Figs 14E</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[465,492,1891,1918]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1137,1162]" captionTargetBox="[151,1402,166,1117]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[151,1402,166,1117]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 15A–D: Megapogon villosus. A: SEM image of atrial layer. B–D: SEM images of spicules; fragmented diactine and cortical triactines (B), microdiactine (C), chiactine (D). Abbreviations: Chi = chiactines; Ctr = cortical triactines; Di= diactines; Mic = microdiactines; Exa = exhalant aperture; Tri = triactines." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3244660/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">15</figureCitation>
C–D). Size: 105.3 ± 
<quantity box="[725,819,1891,1918]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.59" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="15.9">15.9 µm</quantity>
length; 4.5 ± 
<quantity box="[975,1055,1892,1918]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.1 µm</quantity>
width (
<tableCitation box="[1140,1240,1892,1918]" captionStart="TABLE 11" captionStartId="34.[151,239,874,898]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="TABLE 11. Spicule measurements of Megapogon villosus (lectotype BMNH-1907.8.6.146). Measurements from the original description by Jenkin (1908) are included below." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/8DE99893FFF7FF9AE994D257FD6F4FC3" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" tableUuid="8DE99893FFF7FF9AE994D257FD6F4FC3">Table 11</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[151,1437,1279,2026]" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">
<emphasis box="[199,406,1928,1954]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Cortical triactines</emphasis>
: alate triactines with straight unpaired actines longer than the paired actines. Paired actines nearly straight (
<figureCitation box="[326,422,1963,1990]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1137,1162]" captionTargetBox="[151,1402,166,1117]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[151,1402,166,1117]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 15A–D: Megapogon villosus. A: SEM image of atrial layer. B–D: SEM images of spicules; fragmented diactine and cortical triactines (B), microdiactine (C), chiactine (D). Abbreviations: Chi = chiactines; Ctr = cortical triactines; Di= diactines; Mic = microdiactines; Exa = exhalant aperture; Tri = triactines." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3244660/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="234">Fig 15B</figureCitation>
). Size: unpaired actines 289.6 ± 
<quantity box="[785,893,1963,1990]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.885" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="188.5">188.5 µm</quantity>
length, 8.5 ± 
<quantity box="[1047,1127,1964,1990]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.2 µm</quantity>
width; paired actines 158.5 ± 
<quantity box="[174,268,2000,2026]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.22" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="82.2">82.2 µm</quantity>
length, 8.4 ± 
<quantity box="[423,503,2000,2026]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 µm</quantity>
width (
<tableCitation box="[588,688,2000,2026]" captionStart="TABLE 11" captionStartId="34.[151,239,874,898]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="TABLE 11. Spicule measurements of Megapogon villosus (lectotype BMNH-1907.8.6.146). Measurements from the original description by Jenkin (1908) are included below." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/8DE99893FFF7FF9AE994D257FD6F4FC3" pageId="33" pageNumber="234" tableUuid="8DE99893FFF7FF9AE994D257FD6F4FC3">Table 11</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,153,827]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis box="[199,319,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Chiactines</emphasis>
: unpaired actines straight and longer than the paired actines. Apical actine straight, slightly slender, and sharply pointed (
<figureCitation box="[387,485,188,215]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="33.[151,250,1137,1162]" captionTargetBox="[151,1402,166,1117]" captionTargetId="figure@33.[151,1402,166,1117]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURE 15A–D: Megapogon villosus. A: SEM image of atrial layer. B–D: SEM images of spicules; fragmented diactine and cortical triactines (B), microdiactine (C), chiactine (D). Abbreviations: Chi = chiactines; Ctr = cortical triactines; Di= diactines; Mic = microdiactines; Exa = exhalant aperture; Tri = triactines." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3244660/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Fig 15D</figureCitation>
). Size: unpaired actines 466.8 ± 
<quantity box="[852,946,189,215]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.04" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" unit="mm" value="80.4">80.4 µm</quantity>
length, 11.9 ± 
<quantity box="[1115,1195,189,215]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" unit="mm" value="2.9">2.9 µm</quantity>
width; paired actines 199.0 ± 
<quantity box="[245,340,225,251]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.909999999999999" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" unit="mm" value="69.1">69.1 µm</quantity>
length, 10.7 ± 
<quantity box="[513,594,225,251]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" unit="mm" value="1.8">1.8 µm</quantity>
width; apical actines 121.3 ± 33.0 µm length, 10.4 ± 2.0 µm width (
<tableCitation captionStart="TABLE 11" captionStartId="34.[151,239,874,898]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="TABLE 11. Spicule measurements of Megapogon villosus (lectotype BMNH-1907.8.6.146). Measurements from the original description by Jenkin (1908) are included below." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/8DE99893FFF7FF9AE994D257FD6F4FC3" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" tableUuid="8DE99893FFF7FF9AE994D257FD6F4FC3">Table 11</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="235" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,153,827]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,479,296,323]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Distribution and depth.</emphasis>
All the specimens included in 
<bibRefCitation author="Jenkin, C. F." box="[821,977,297,323]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" pagination="1 - 49" refId="ref27105" refString="Jenkin, C. F. (1908) Porifera. III. Calcarea. National Antarctic Expedition, 1901 - 1904, Natural History, 4, Zoology, 1 - 49, pls. XXVII-XXXVIII." type="journal article" year="1908">Jenkin (1908)</bibRefCitation>
, were taken around Winter Quarters Bay, and most of them from shallow waters.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,153,827]" box="[199,659,368,395]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,494,368,395]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Molecular identification.</emphasis>
Not available.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="235" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,153,827]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,405,431]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Remarks.</emphasis>
Among the species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jenkin" authorityYear="1908" box="[568,702,406,431]" class="Calcarea" family="Achramorphidae" genus="Megapogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leucosolenida" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[568,702,406,431]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Megapogon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described from the Antarctic, 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Burton" authorityYear="1963" box="[1037,1159,405,431]" class="Calcarea" family="Achramorphidae" genus="Megapogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leucosolenida" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="villosus">
<emphasis box="[1037,1159,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">M. villosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only one that presents a strongly hispid surface due to the presence of very long diactines. These diactines were difficult to measure because they were broken but based on the original description (
<bibRefCitation author="Jenkin, C. F." box="[864,1004,477,503]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" pagination="1 - 49" refId="ref27105" refString="Jenkin, C. F. (1908) Porifera. III. Calcarea. National Antarctic Expedition, 1901 - 1904, Natural History, 4, Zoology, 1 - 49, pls. XXVII-XXXVIII." type="journal article" year="1908">Jenkin 1908</bibRefCitation>
), they can reach up to 
<quantity box="[1253,1353,476,503]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" unit="mm" value="1500.0">1500 µm</quantity>
length, which is as long as in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Polejaeff" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[398,525,513,539]" class="Calcarea" family="Achramorphidae" genus="Megapogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leucosolenida" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="crucifer">
<emphasis box="[398,525,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">M. crucifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingRegion box="[633,716,513,539]" country="Portugal" name="Acores" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Azores</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,153,827]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
The four specimens examined here were the same used by 
<bibRefCitation author="Jenkin, C. F." box="[885,1042,549,575]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" pagination="1 - 49" refId="ref27105" refString="Jenkin, C. F. (1908) Porifera. III. Calcarea. National Antarctic Expedition, 1901 - 1904, Natural History, 4, Zoology, 1 - 49, pls. XXVII-XXXVIII." type="journal article" year="1908">Jenkin (1908)</bibRefCitation>
to describe the species, and those specimens labelled as cotype are now erected as 
<typeStatus box="[697,848,585,611]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">paralectotype</typeStatus>
(recommendation 74F of the ICZN).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,153,827]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
The oscular region could not be examined, but according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Jenkin, C. F." box="[871,1028,621,647]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" pagination="1 - 49" refId="ref27105" refString="Jenkin, C. F. (1908) Porifera. III. Calcarea. National Antarctic Expedition, 1901 - 1904, Natural History, 4, Zoology, 1 - 49, pls. XXVII-XXXVIII." type="journal article" year="1908">Jenkin (1908)</bibRefCitation>
, the osculum is at the end of a collar built up by tetractines laying tangentially on the inside, with their unpaired actines pointing downwards and the apical actines projecting into the atrium. On the outside there are also tangentially arranged triactines and a few special diactines placed horizontally (
<bibRefCitation author="Jenkin, C. F." box="[492,635,729,755]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" pagination="1 - 49" refId="ref27105" refString="Jenkin, C. F. (1908) Porifera. III. Calcarea. National Antarctic Expedition, 1901 - 1904, Natural History, 4, Zoology, 1 - 49, pls. XXVII-XXXVIII." type="journal article" year="1908">Jenkin 1908</bibRefCitation>
). These horizontal diactines have not been mentioned before in any of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jenkin" authorityYear="1908" box="[192,326,766,791]" class="Calcarea" family="Achramorphidae" genus="Megapogon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leucosolenida" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[192,326,766,791]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Megapogon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. However, we would need more material where the oscular area is included, to examine this character in greater detail.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
